rdf:Description.lla:note: The Official Log describes the continous rebellious acts of the four men: Docherty, Smith, Sykes, and McCallum
Official Log describes him trying to desert on 1873-02-11 abord another ship, but he was found out
According to the Official Log, he lied about being a sailor in order to travel to England. It was discovered on the 1872-12-15 that he was actually a blacksmith
Official Log says "he is far from being an able seaman"
In Port of joining it says "found at mouth (of) Paraiba River"--He was discovered on board during the night
Under Cause says "Wanted home", and he arrived "too late to appear before shipping master"
